name: Cucumber and Melon Salad with Chile and Honey

steps.instruction:
From [here](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/cucumber-and-melon-salad-with-chile-and-honey)

### Prep
- Thinly slice the jalapeo 
- English Hothouse Cucumber should be halved crosswise, then lengthwise, seeds scooped out with a spoon

### Steps
1. Preheat oven to 350.
2. Toast pistachios on a rimmed baking sheet, tossing once, until golden brown, 79 minutes.
3. Let cool, then finely chop 2 Tbsp. pistachios. Leave remaining nuts whole; set aside
4. Whisk chopped pistachios, chile, vinegar, and honey in a small bowl
5. Gradually stream in oil, whisking constantly until emulsified; generously season dressing with salt and pepper.
6. Using a mandoline, shave cucumber and honeydew lengthwise (or thinly slice with a knife). Place in a large bowl
7. Set blade to a slightly wider setting; shave cheese into planks. Add to bowl along with basil and reserved pistachios; drizzle dressing over and toss gently. Season with salt and pepper.

ingredients.note: Or cantaloupe, with the rind removed
Its salted dry ricotta, or you can use feta
